specially since tests throw Throwable. I wonder if I should avoid using reflection and lean towards leveraging MethodHandles instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering resource management**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to handle a few technical details. I need the `URLConnection.getInputStream throws IOException` signature and how to override without using throws, along with the `connect` method. There might be a resource URL issue in the native context, but that’s manageable. I also need to clear the cache with `ResourceBundle.clearCache(bundleClassLoader)`, and I'm checking locale and TCCL settings. It seems modifying resources isn't necessary, but I can definitely write a file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9azmoJrGlZTRK7pRy2KjewKt|fc_09ab6edfd708da5c016a01f944d9648193a4defb03e893c213", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/MessageFactoryTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage jakarta_platform.jakarta_jakartaee_api;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLConnection;\nimport java.net.URLStreamHandler;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Iterator;\nimport java.util.Locale;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.ResourceBundle;\n\nimport jakarta.faces.application.Application;\nimport jakarta.faces.application.ApplicationWrapper;\nimport jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\nimport jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage.Severity;\nimport jakarta.faces.component.UIViewRoot;\nimport jakarta.faces.context.ExternalContext;\nimport jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\nimport jakarta.faces.context.ResponseStream;\nimport jakarta.faces.context.ResponseWriter;\nimport jakarta.faces.lifecycle.Lifecycle;\nimport jakarta.faces.render.RenderKit;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class MessageFactoryTest {\n    private static final String MESSAGE_FACTORY_CLASS = \"jakarta.faces.webapp.MessageFactory\";\n    private static final String APPLICATION_BUNDLE = \"jakarta_platform.jakarta_jakartaee_api.MessageFactoryMessages\";\n    private static final String APPLICATION_BUNDLE_RESOURCE =\n            \"jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/MessageFactoryMessages.properties\";\n    private static final String FACES_BUNDLE_RESOURCE = \"jakarta/faces/Messages.properties\";\n    private static final String MOJARRA_BUNDLE_RESOURCE = \"com/sun/faces/resources/Messages.properties\";\n\n    @Test\n    public void getMessageUsesConfiguredApplicationBundle() throws Throwable {\n        try (TestFacesContext context = TestFacesContext.activate(new TestApplication(APPLICATION_BUNDLE))) {\n            FacesMessage message = getMessage(\"jakarta.faces.component.UIInput.REQUIRED\", \"Custom Label\");\n\n            assertThat(message.getSummary()).isEqualTo(\"Application bundle says Custom Label is required\");\n            assertThat(message.getSeverity()).isEqualTo(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR);\n            assertThat(context.getApplication().getMessageBundle()).isEqualTo(APPLICATION_BUNDLE);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void getMessageFallsBackToFacesMessagesBundleWhenApplicationBundleIsNotConfigured() throws Throwable {\n        try (TestFacesContext context = TestFacesContext.activate(new TestApplication(null))) {\n            FacesMessage message = getMessage(\"jakarta.faces.component.UIInput.REQUIRED\", \"Standard Label\");\n\n  