ext\":\"**Considering ResourceBundle issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking there might be a problem with how dynamic access metadata for resources is counted when the bundle exists. It probably instruments the `getBundle` call before any exceptions are thrown, which is important for tests to pass. \\n\\nI have concerns about the `URL` stream handler and `ResourceBundle`. The `PropertyResourceBundle` reads streams fine, but I wonder if `ResourceBundle.Control` handles candidate locales correctly. It seems it might try loading a class bundle first, which could lead to issues. I’ll check if `ClassLoader.getResources` is being used instead of `getResource`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing coverage issues with ResourceBundle**\\n\\nI see a potential problem with calling `ResourceBundle.clearCache(bundleClassLoader)` during close. If the test throws an error before the context is constructed after setting the TCCL, it might not close properly. \\n\\nI need to inspect the dynamic coverage report since it seems like no tests have run. I wonder if there's a way to keep old tests that cover component classes, while focusing on the active ones. Deleting those tests might reduce coverage for `component.MessageFactory`, so I should check the report for it.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_m6vvadEijIv38FMd7GddSHAL|fc_09ab6edfd708da5c016a01f9696b0481939e3e55037c1e3f03", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "grep -n 'jakarta.faces.component.MessageFactory\\|jakarta.faces.convert.MessageFactory\\|jakarta.faces.validator.MessageFactory\\|jakarta.faces.webapp.MessageFactory' tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2697, "output": 976, "cacheRead": 49664, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53337, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "time