w file. I think it's best to preserve the original file to keep things neat. If the external native test fails, that shouldn't be our problem since it's existing. My first attempt fixed a missing resource in MessageFactoryTest, but reverting could cause issues. I’m considering keeping an in-memory fix and potentially writing a less invasive component from the current work. I'll copy the current content to a new file for now.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_c8sp8dib1wO6vHUW82fmFSVY|fc_09ab6edfd708da5c016a01f981145c81938f105b4070bc4f0a", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "cp tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/MessageFactoryTest.java tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/WebappMessageFactoryTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2551, "output": 1251, "cacheRead": 53248, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57050, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778514285866, "responseId": "resp_09ab6edfd708da5c016a01f96eb50c8193b56612e4476fe01a"}}
