"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering ResourceBundle issues**\\n\\nI think I need to double-check if `ResourceBundle.clearCache(bundleClassLoader)` will clear only the original cache and not the fallback. It might be important to see if tests are executed in parallel since they set the global TCCL, default locale, and static FacesContext. JUnit might not support this parallel execution. I should also see if importing `HashMap` in the Webapp for the classloader is necessary. Additionally, I’m pondering whether to use `invokeWithArguments` to avoid a `WrongMethodTypeException` while keeping polymorphic calls in mind.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Java 21 testing concerns**\\n\\nI'm considering whether my tests running on the JVM under Java 21 should address package-private targets in dependency classes that have a module. If the jars contain `module-info`, would that affect how I interact with them? For example, does `jakarta.jakartaee-api` include module-info? I’m checking if I'm dealing with an unnamed module on the classpath, but it seems Gradle isn’t using a module path. Also, I might need to know if `privateLookupIn` for a package-private top-level class necessitates the target class being public.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented active-class coverage for `jakarta.faces.webapp.MessageFactory`.\n\nChanges:\n- Added `tests/src/jakarta.platform/jakarta.jakartaee-api/10.0.0/src/test/java/jakarta_platform/jakarta_jakartaee_api/WebappMessageFactoryTest.java`\n  - Directly exercises `jakarta.faces.webapp.MessageFactory.getMessage(Locale, String, Object...)`.\n  - Covers all three resource-bundle paths:\n    - configured application bundle\n    - fallback to `jakarta.faces.Messages`\n    - fallback to Mojarra bundle\n  - Uses an in-memory `ClassLoader` for resource bundles so the tests do not depend on Native Image resource inclusion.\n\n- Kept/refined existing `MessageFactoryTest.java`\n  - Preserves existing component-message coverage.\n  - Also uses the in-memory resource bundle loader to avoid classpath resource issues.\n\nI did not run or compile tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09ab6edfd708da5c016a01f9c75a888193b253d54d67ba5375\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 599, "output": 844, "cacheRead": 62976, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 64419, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778514360509, "responseId": "resp_09ab6edfd708da5c016a01f9b96a6c8193bc69d4669bf3d04e"}, "toolResults": []}
